about.description:
Googletrans is a free and unlimited python library that implemented Google Translate API. This uses the Google Translate Ajax API to make calls to such methods as detect and translate.
Compatible with Python 2.7+ and 3.4+. (Note: Python 2 support will be dropped in the next major release.)
about.summary: Free Google Translate API for Python. Translates totally free of charge.

name: googletrans
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "googletrans" %}
{% set version = "2.4.0" %}
{% set file_ext = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_value = "bb4e2a6ee72a24870e696a14238b7305f855a05206ecae10bd50052651984cc5" %}


package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  '{{ hash_type }}': '{{ hash_value }}'

build:
  noarch_python: True
  preserve_egg_dir: True
  number: 1000
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pip
    - requests
  run:
    - python
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - googletrans


about:
  home: https://github.com/ssut/py-googletrans
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Free Google Translate API for Python. Translates totally free of charge.'
  description: "Googletrans is a free and unlimited python library that implemented Google Translate API. This uses the Google Translate Ajax API to make calls to such methods as detect and translate.\nCompatible with Python 2.7+ and 3.4+. (Note: Python 2 support will be dropped in the next major release.)"
  doc_url: https://github.com/ssut/py-googletrans
  dev_url: https://py-googletrans.readthedocs.io/en/latest/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - SekouD
